\v 1 King Ahasuerus did a payment of tax on all the people who were in all the districts of his kingdom that is all the land, coastal area to the island area.
\v 2 And all the proceeds that were obtained King Ahasueros because of his greatness and power were written in the book called, "Official writings that were done by the Kings of Media and Persia.' Various things that were done by Mordecai, the man who was given entitlement by the king, also were written in that book.
